---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import { sitePath } from "../../lib/playground/links";

const frontmatter = {
  title: "Use Cases",
  description:
    "Use cases for applying DCL to compiler-verifiable architecture and governance problems.",
};
---

<DocsLayout frontmatter={frontmatter}>
  <h1>Use Cases</h1>
  <p>
    DCL is a language for describing business capabilities in a way that is
    explicit, analyzable, and compiler-verifiable. While it was designed around
    capabilities, intents, outcomes, policies, and effects, those same concepts
    apply to a wide range of architecture and governance problems.
  </p>
  <p>
    Use cases show how DCL can be applied beyond traditional documentation,
    including AI governance, regulated systems, event-driven architecture,
    long-running workflows, and enterprise capability modelling.
  </p>

  <section class="construct-card">
    <h2>AI Governance &amp; Regulatory Compliance</h2>
    <p>
      Use DCL to describe what AI-enabled capabilities do, which actors are
      involved, what outcomes are possible, which policies apply, and what
      effects or audit evidence must be produced.
    </p>
    <p class="inline-actions">
      <a class="button secondary" href={sitePath("/use-cases/ai-governance-regulatory-compliance/")}>
        Read the use case
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
